title: Plan a stop at the updated Diamond Point Airstrip and enjoy the updated scenery!
description:
Diamond Point Airport is a private community airport located on the northeast corner of Miller Peninsula in Clallam County, Washington, 8 mi (13 km) east of Sequim. It opened in August 1965.

This updated created by ORBX adds a lot of detail to this airstrip which makes it super interesting, especially if you love the Cub Crafter aircraft and performing a bush trip.
